# Adversary fixture: FM1 — @base with relative @id
# Failure mode: implementations that ignore @base in context, or that only
#   apply @base to properties but not to the node @id, will produce an
#   incorrect absolute IRI or reject the document.
# JSON-LD 1.1 §6.1 (IRI expansion): a relative IRI in @id is resolved
#   against the in-scope base IRI established by @base in the active context.
# Expected: one triple with subject http://example.org/base/doc
# spec-ref: W3C JSON-LD 1.1 §4.1.2, §6.1 IRI Expansion algorithm step 7
# divergence-hypothesis: AcceptRejectSplit — parsers that skip @base resolution
#   on node @id emit the relative IRI or reject; conformant parsers resolve.
outcome: accept
fact-count: 1
ACCEPT
<http://example.org/base/doc> <http://schema.org/name> "Test Document" .
